<span class="postbody">EDIT: bleh sentences in wronfg place at the start <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Excellent for the level I must admit, but I am unsure why you are not wearing the bloodweave cap? The stats are better than the circlet, with a minor penalty to Fire resist.  I myself  prefer the free hair look, but can't remeber if the bloodweave has a graphic or not.  Unless it's about the hair, I'd certainly change hats. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
The dagger will serve well for quite a while, unless you can find a 1hb or better yet a faster dagger to play with that has some int on it.  Also what race?  The Dark Elf enc has a very nice dagger to quest, something to get a group and go have some fun with (if there are enough around in teh newb zone). <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  Had a wiz using the dagger up into my 40's or maybe it was 30's? <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  Otherwise . . . umm . . . maybe these?
<br />

<br />
Pierce
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Dagger of Dropping</span>  (effect of weaken, 4 / 22, Magic)
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Darkedged Dirk</span> (3 str 3 int 10 mana, 6 / 23, Magic Lore)
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Coldain Velium Dagger</span> (effect 75 pt dd at lev 1, 4 / 19, Magic) purchase in thurgadin (velious city dwarves) for 75p
<br />

<br />
1 Hand Blunt
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Surveyor's Rod</span> (Wis 4 Int 4, 5 / 20, Magic)
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Golden Mace</span> (str 4 agi 4 wis 4 int 4, 6 / 30, Magic)
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Di'zok Sceptre of Authority</span> (ac 10 wis 5 int 5 mana 25 Mr 5, Magic)
<br />

<br />
I think most of these have dropped in price quite a bit.  Getting into Thurg might be tough, but it's not too bad a run, and if you get a SoW and Invis should be able to make it easily.  Some of the others depends on if they are available in Bazaar (if you have PoP) for reasonable price.  I used a crystal grinder for quite a while myself, and they are also fairly cheap, and decent delay dmg for newb hunter. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
You are in for some fun, I avoided any DoT weapons, in case you decide to try for the Stun and run idea.  Although with the changes to pre level 10 the zergling approach seems to have been accepted. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
